How to Use WooCommerce with Elementor?

Launched in 2011, WooCommerce adds e-commerce functionality to WordPress websites. However, it might lack features in terms of design customization. And page builders like Elementor join the game!

Is it possible to make an off-the-charts WooCommerce website while building it with Elementor? Absolutely! For your convenience, we’ve prepared a quick list with the first steps on how to start using them in a matter of clicks:

Install and activate the WooCommerce plugin from your WordPress dashboard.

Set up your WooCommerce store:

Add basic information about your shop;

Set up WooCommerce payment options;

Configure shipping settings.

Install and activate the Elementor plugin if you haven’t done so already.

Edit the WooCommerce pages with Elementor. For example, you can customize the WooCommerce Shop page, Product pages, Cart page, and My Account page.

Add and customize WooCommerce Elementor widgets: Add to Cart, Short Description, Product Categories, Checkout, My Account, Product Rating, and others.

